{
  "page": "King of the True Men",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>King of the True Men</b> was an ancient, vainglorious title held by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Shett\" title=\"House Shett\">House Shett</a>, the former rulers of <a href=\"/index.php/Gulltown\" title=\"Gulltown\">Gulltown</a>, which supposedly went back ten thousand years to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dawn_Age\" title=\"Dawn Age\">Dawn Age</a>. After the death of King <a href=\"/index.php/Osgood_III_Shett\" title=\"Osgood III Shett\">Osgood III Shett</a>, the Shett crown was claimed by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Grafton_(Andal_invader)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gerold Grafton (Andal invader)\">Gerold Grafton</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Grafton\" title=\"House Grafton\">Graftons</a> henceforth ruled the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_the_True_Men&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Vale.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"pa